
New Features in taskd 1.0.0.alpha

  - Functioning sync algorithm
  - IPv4 and IPv6 support
  - TLS
  - JSON Support
  - CRL Support
  - Client allow/deny lists
  - Documentation
  - Requires libuuid

  Please refer to the ChangeLog file for full details.  There are too many to
  list here.

New configuration options in taskd 1.0.0.alpha

  - $TASKDDATA specifies the data root directory, otherwise '--data <root>' is
    needed for most commands.
  - Supports 'ip.log' to turn on/off logging of client IP address and port.
  - Sending a HUP signal to the task server forces a configuration file reload.
  - Added more statistics.

---

Taskd has been built and tested on the following configurations:

  * OS X 10.8 Mountain Lion
  * Debian 6.0 Squeeze (stable)
  * Ubuntu 10.04 Lucid Lynx and 13.04 Raring Ringtail
  * Arch Linux
  * Cygwin 1.7

---

While taskd has undergone testing, bugs are sure to remain.  If you encounter a
bug, please enter a new issue at:

  http://taskwarrior.org/projects/taskwarrior/issues/new

Or you can also report the issue in the forums at:

  http://taskwarrior.org/projects/taskwarrior/boards

Or just send a message to:

  support@taskwarrior.org

Thank you.

